resources.string:
Introduction
 During the game, a group of bubbles will fall from the top of game area, and you can move, revolve, or turn the bubble group to let them stay in right station. When some of bubbles stop and others could continue falling, the others could keep on move, revolve, or turn. When all bubbles stopped, if the number of border upon bubbles, whose attribute are same, is great or equal to the Minimum Bubble Number for Destroy, these bubbles will be destroyed.

 Score
 When the bubble number achieve the Minimum Bubble Number for Destroy, 1 score for each bubble; For exceed part, the score will be double for each bubble; When bubbles continue destroyed, the score will be double.

 Orientation Change
 When the orientation of screen changed, the station of bubbles will be adjusted in runtime. Handing bubbles will fall to ground.

 Touch Screen Operation
 Draw a clockwise line on screen to clockwise-revolve the falling bubble group;
 Draw a anticlockwise line on screen to anticlockwise-revolve the falling bubble group;
 Draw a vertical line on screen to vertical-turn the falling bubble group;
 Draw a horizontal line on screen to horizontal-turn the falling bubble group;
 Touch the left or right area of the falling bubble group to move it to left or right;
 Touch the down area of the falling bubble group to accelerate down speed.

 Key Operation
 C key to clockwise-revolve the falling bubble group;
 A key to anticlockwise-revolve the falling bubble group;
 V key to vertical-turn the falling bubble group;
 H key to horizontal-turn the falling bubble group;
 Left, Right key to move the falling bubble group to left or right;
 Down key to accelerate down speed;
 Up key is same as C key by default, and could be configured.

 Difficult Setting
 the Color and Shape Mode, Destroy Mode, Minimum Bubble Number for Destroy, Bubble Number on Short Line, Bubble Number on Long Line could be set to adjust the difficult of game. All setting could be took effect in runtime.

 About Variety Bubble
